  "prompt": "Account opening in Zerodha states 48 hours, I have submitted all documents and it has been 10 days with no luck. Pathetic support, how to escalate?",
  "response": "I understand your frustration with the delay in your Zerodha account opening process. Here's what you can do to escalate the issue:\n\n### **Steps to Escalate the Issue**\n1. **Contact Zerodha Support Directly**  \n   - Visit the **[Zerodha Support Page](https://support.zerodha.com)** and raise a ticket if you haven\u2019t already.  \n   - Email them at `support@zerodha.com`. Include all details like your registered mobile number, PAN, and the date when you submitted the documents.  \n\n2. **Use the Zerodha Console**  \n   - Log in to the **[Zerodha Console](https://console.zerodha.com/)** and check the status of your application. If there\u2019s an issue, it might be mentioned there.  \n\n3. **Reach Out on Social Media**  \n   - Tweet to Zerodha\u2019s official Twitter handle **[@zerodhaonline](https://twitter.com/zerodhaonline)**. Public posts often get quicker responses.  \n\n4. **Call Customer Care**  \n   - Call Zerodha\u2019s helpline: **+91-80-4040-2020** (Mon-Fri, 9:30 AM to 6:30 PM).  \n   - Be persistent and ask for a resolution timeline.  \n\n5. **Visit a Branch (If Possible)**  \n   - If you\u2019re near a Zerodha branch, visit in person with your documents to expedite the process.  \n\n6. **File a Complaint with SEBI**  \n   - If all else fails, you can escalate the issue to the Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI) via their **[SCORES platform](https://scores.gov.in/)**.  \n\n### **Tips for Faster Resolution**  \n- Ensure all submitted documents are clear and meet Zerodha\u2019s requirements (e.g., PAN, Aadhaar, Proof of Address).  \n- Follow up daily via email or phone.  \n\nHopefully, one of these steps will help resolve the issue quickly. Let me know if you need further assistance!",
